The paper deals with the logical foundations of ACL2(r), a variant of ACL2 that supports irrational real and complex numbers. It discusses the definitions of concepts from real analysis, such as continuity, differentiability, and integrability, in the context of non-standard analysis (NSA) and internal set theory (IST). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Other likely sub-categories include cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.MS (Mathematical Software), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
